            <entry xml:id="entry_cyraǧ" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyraǧ</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ciraǧ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лучина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>wicker lamp</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>свеча</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>candle</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">also</note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лампа</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">also</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>lamp</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>cyraǧdaræn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>подсвечник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>candlestick</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cyraǧ næm ḱī sūʒy fæsxærd?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто у нас зажигает лучину после ужина?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>who among us lights a wicker lamp after dinner?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ficcag næ Digori adæn suǧtoncæ næzi ciraǧ; oj fæste bazudtoncæ sojnin
                            ciraǧ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>прежде наш дигорский народ зажигал сосновую лучину; после этого
                                узнали сальную свечу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>before our Digor people lit a pine torch; after that we learned the
                                greasy candle</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ciraǧ... iscæfstæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лампа зажглась</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the lamp lit</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æxsæv cyraǧdaræj fæxattæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в ночь ты ходил в качестве носителя светильника</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in the night you walked as a light bearer</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Общее переднеазиатское слово. Засвидетельствовано уже в
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*čirāǧ(čr'γ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>лампа</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>cirau</w>
                        <gloss><q>лампа</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. далее <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čirāǧ</w>
                        <gloss><q>светильник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>лампа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>свеча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>факел</q></gloss></mentioned> и т. п., <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraǧ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w>čiraq</w></mentioned>; бытует также в языках; в кавказских: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraq</w>
                        <gloss><q>свеча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>лампа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraxi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>čiraǧdani</w>
                        <gloss><q>свеча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>факел</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. Источником всех этих форм
                    следует считать <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čirāǧ</w></mentioned>. Для осетинского надо, однако, иметь в виду и
                    возможность усвоения из согдийского. Происхождение слова не выяснено. Исходное
                    значение было, возможно, ‘светлячок’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čīraka-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čīrika-</w>
                        <gloss><q>сверчок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>čillakā-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čilamīlikā</w>
                        <gloss><q>ein leuchtendes fliegendes Insekt</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>Blitz</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_PW"/></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 78</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A common Western Asian word. It is attested so far in <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*čirāǧ(čr'γ)</w>
                        <gloss><q>lamp</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>cirau</w>
                        <gloss><q>lamp</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. further <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čirāǧ</w>
                        <gloss><q>lamp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>candle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cresset</q></gloss></mentioned> etc., <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraǧ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w>čiraq</w></mentioned>; it is found also in languages; in Caucasian
                    languages: <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraq</w>
                        <gloss><q>candle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>lamp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>čiraxi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>čiraǧdani</w>
                        <gloss><q>lamp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cresset</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The source of all these forms
                    should be considered <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čirāǧ</w></mentioned>. For the Ossetic, however, one must bear in mind
                    the possibility of borrowing from the Sogdian. The origin of the word has not
                    been clarified. The original meaning was possibly ‘firefly’; cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čīraka-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čīrika-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cricket</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>čillakā-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čilamīlikā</w>
                        <gloss><q>ein leuchtendes fliegendes Insekt</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>Blitz</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_PW"/></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 78</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
